# Walkthrough - Universal Search & Chat Revamp

I have successfully pulled the repository and implemented **Universal Search** and **Revamped Chat Logic**.

## New Features
1.  **Universal Default**: The "Universal Search" mode is now enabled by default.
2.  **Global Context**: You can now chat without selecting any nodes. The AI will use **all** node summaries in the graph as context.
3.  **Focused Context**: If you select nodes, the AI automatically focuses **only** on those nodes.
4.  **UI Indicators**: The chat header now clearly shows "Global Context (All Nodes)" or "Focused Context (X Nodes)".
5.  **Robust Online Search**: Supports **Google Custom Search API** (requires keys) for reliability, with an automatic fallback to the scraper.
6.  **Smart Ingestion**: Automatically creates "External Research" nodes from search results.
7.  **Smart Citations**: Answers use inline Markdown links `[Title](URL)` for easy referencing.

